ed (don\'t use standard C++ include paths), but then `-cxx-isystem` paths are added for libstdc++ headers. This is contradictory.\n\n3. **Library Path Issues**: \n   - The path `/out/install.d/lib64/libstdc++.a` may not exist (libstdc++ was installed to `/out/install.d/lib/../lib32/` based on the log)\n   - Architecture mismatch: Building for x86_64 but libstdc++ was built for 32-bit (`lib32` directory)\n\n4. **Compiler Compatibility**: Using AFL++\'s `afl-clang-fast++` which is based on Clang, trying to link with GCC\'s libstdc++.\n\n**Recommended Fix Strategies:**\n\n1. **Standard Library Consistency**: Either:\n   - Remove `-stdlib=libc++` to use libstdc++ consistently\n   - OR link against libc++ instead of libstdc++.a\n\n2. **Fix Library Paths**: \n   - Correct the library path to `/out/install.d/lib32/libstdc++.a` or `/out/install.d/lib32/libstdc++.so`\n   - Ensure 64-bit library is available if needed\n\n3. **Header Configuration**: \n   - Remove `-nostdinc++` if using libstdc++ headers\n   - OR properly configure include paths for libc++ if using that\n\n4. **Build Script Analysis**: Examine the `build.sh` script in the project configuration to understand the intended build process.\n\n**Contextual Information:**\n- Project: libstdcpp (GCC\'s C++ standard library)\n- Engine: AFL++ (afl-clang-fast++)\n- Sanitizer: Address Sanitizer\n- Architecture: x86_64\n- The libstdc++ library was successfully built in 32-bit mode (`lib32` directories)\n\n**Priority Fixes:**\n1. Resolve the standard library conflict (libc++ vs libstdc++)\n2. Fix library and header paths\n3. Ensure architecture consistency (32-bit vs 64-bit libraries)\n\n**Success Metrics:**\nThe fuzzer compilation should produce a working binary that links correctly against the built libstdc++ library with AFL++ instrumentation and address sanitizer enabled.\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] First build attempt failed with same error as original: Makefile:4764: all-gcc Error 2. The build progressed through configuration and compilation but failed during GCC build stage. Many struct/class mismatch warnings appear but are not the root cause. Need to examine earlier compilation errors to understand why all-gcc target fails.\n- [Attempt 1] Initial environment setup succeeded in fixing the GCC compilation error. The libstdc++ library was successfully built and installed. The failure has now shifted to the fuzzer compilation/linking stage, which is a different problem (likely linker flags or library paths). This represents significant progress from the original build failure.\n- [Attempt 1] Excellent progress: Build successfully completed libstdc++ compilation and installation, moving past the original gcc compilation failure. The error stage has advanced from gcc compilation to fuzzer compilation, representing significant forward movement in the build pipeline. The libstdc++ library was built successfully.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2023 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:6d7dd44ebec7ae27386a7b8a37ce0e827fe1604c33ef5a3a009a10f0fdf7bc34\nRUN sed -i -e \'s/^# deb-src/deb-src/g\' /etc/apt/sources.list\nRUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y make autoconf automake libtool\nRUN apt build-dep -y g++-10\nRUN git clone  git://gcc.gnu.org/git/gcc.git libstdcpp\nWORKDIR libstdcpp\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\nADD https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pauldreik/stdfuzz/main/format/one-arg.cpp $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2023 Google LLC\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\nSRCDIR=$SRC/libstdcpp\nBUILDDIR=$OUT/build.d\nINSTALLDIR=$OUT/install.d\nmkdir -p $BUILDDIR $INSTALLDIR\n\n(\n    cd $BUILDDIR\n    CXX= CC= CXXFLAGS= CFLAGS= $SRCDIR/configure \\\n       --disable-bootstrap \\\n       --prefix=$INSTALLDIR \\\n       --enable-languages=c++\n    make -j$(nproc)\n    make -j$(nproc) install-target-libstdc++-v3\n)\n\nfor fuzzsrcfile in /src/*.cpp; do\n    targetfile=$(basename $fuzzsrcfile .cpp)\n    $CXX \\\n\t$CXXFLAGS \\\n\t-std=c++20 \\\n\t-nostdinc++ \\\n\t-cxx-isystem $( echo $INSTALLDIR/include/c++/*/ ) \\\n\t-cxx-isystem $( echo $INSTALLDIR/include/c++/*/x86_64-pc-linux-gnu ) \\\n\t$fuzzsrcfile \\\n\t-o $OUT/$targetfile \\\n\t$LIB_FUZZING_ENGINE \\\n\t$INSTALLDIR/lib64/libstdc++.a\ndone\n\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://gcc.gnu.org/"\nlanguage: c++\nprimary_contact: "pauldreikossfuzz@gmail.com"\nauto_ccs:\n - "jwakely.gcc@gmail.com"\nmain_repo: "git://gcc.gnu.org/git/gcc.git"\nfile_github_issue: false\narchitectures:\n - x86_64\nsanitizers:\n - address\n - undefined\nfuzzing_engines:\n  - libfuzzer\n  - afl\n  - honggfuzz